  "text": "It is shown that under suitable assumptions, (θ n ,β n0 ,β n ) is a consistent estimator of (θ,β 0 ,β). The proofs are available in C. These results have been proved by [CITATION_1] for the quantile-based classifier with the 0-1 loss function. The proof given by them has been adapted to take into account the additional parameters (β 0 , β) and the change of the loss function from the 0-1 loss function to the binomial loss function. Assumption 2 is added in addition to Assumption 1 made by [CITATION_2] . The linear discriminant function or metalearner C(z | β 0 , β) in Equation (6), the discriminant function with multiplicative interactions, and the polynomial discriminant function used in polynomial kernel SVM all satisfy Assumption 2.",
